version_description: Pretty easy, and common, chord progression to learn. Not much difference from the real song. I put these as intermediate just because of the B minor chord and the capo on 2nd, also has a decently challenging strumming pattern. Plays at 92 BPM with a 4/4 time signature.
This version is as simple as possible to play on acoustic guitar in standard tuning.
All chords should be palm-muted for the best sound, but that isn't crucial, if you don't want to.
